OL,3,C'More work to be done' to support
OL,4,Cunpaid carers in Jersey
OL,6,FHowever, ESSH's report states that
OL,7,F"the Social Security Fund is balanced
OL,8,Fby the general principle that no one
OL,9,Fcan receive an amount totalling more
OL,10,Fthan 100% of the standard rate of any
OL,11,Fcontributory benefit. Because it's a
OL,12,Fcontributory scheme, a person can't
OL,13,Fclaim two benefits based on one set of
OL,14,Fcontributions."
OL,16,FIf Mark were to claim both his full
OL,17,Fpension and the full HCA allowance, it
OL,18,Fwould total more than 100% of the
OL,19,F"standard rate" of a single
OL,20,Fcontributory benefit.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/12
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
