OL,3,C'More work to be done' to support
OL,4,Cunpaid carers in Jersey
OL,6,FIn a statement, Carers Jersey say they
OL,7,F"welcome" these updates and the
OL,8,Fproductive conversations they have had
OL,9,Fwith the Minister for Social Security,
OL,10,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, throughout the
OL,11,Fprocess of the review.
OL,13,F"We are delighted that much work has
OL,14,Fbeen undertaken in a short space of
OL,15,Ftime", they explain, adding "the
OL,16,FMinister's commitment goes some way to
OL,17,Facknowledging and recognising the
OL,18,Fexistence of unpaid carers and the
OL,19,Fplight which a vast number of them
OL,20,Fface. This is, indeed, a step in the
OL,21,Fright direction.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G10/12
